    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "FROM: SAC, Louisville",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "SUBJECT: ALF E. HIXENBAUGH'S \"Photographs",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "of Flying Saucers;",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "INFORMATION CONCERNING",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "On June 28, 1950, the Louisville Times, a newspaper of general",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "circulation published at Louisville, Kentucky, carried a two-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "column cut showing three frames of a movie camera film of what",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "purported to be a moving picture of a flying saucer. The photo-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "graphs, taken by ALF (AL) HIXENBAUGH, Times staff photographer,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "were taken, HIXENBAUGH said, on a 16 mm magazine-loading movie",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "camera.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "The news article, accompanying the photographs, stated HIXENBAUGH",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "took 50 feet of film in which \"the bright flying object shows",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "clearly.\" The photographer, according to the article, was at",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "Longest and Everett Avenues near his home, 2205 Longest, at 4:15",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "p.m., June 27, 1950, on his way to take some moving pictures of",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "birds. The article relates that HIXENBAUGH \"suddenly heard the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "roar of a big plane -- a twin-motored DC-3 -- and glanced over-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "head. At first he thought it was a jet plane then he looked to",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "the west of the plant, which was flying southwest toward Standi-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "ford Field -- and saw the large disk. It had a slight corona",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "around it and seemed to be lower than the plane.\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "According to HIXENBAUGH, \"the object appeared \"motionless for about",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "ten seconds ... then it began to get smaller, finally vanishing into",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "the west.\" The article notes that while the \"saucer\" appeared on",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "all the film HIXENBAUGH took, the airplane was out of the picture",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "field quickly, appearing on only about 10 feet. HIXENBAUGH, accord-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "ing to the article, advised military officers at Godman Field who",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "in turn notified flight headquarters at Wright-Patterson Field.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "A copy of the newspaper article and photographs are being forwarded",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "to the Bureau as enclosures.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "A subsequent newspaper article stated that representatives of the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "military would fly to Louisville to examine the films. In addition",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "to being printed in the Louisville Times, the movie film taken by",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "text": "HIXENBAUGH was carried on a national television network and received",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "text": "national comment from WALTER WINCHELL. HIXENBAUGH has received tele-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 47,
      "text": "phonic and written queries concerning subject matter of the picture",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
